  "texts": [
    "against killing people.",
    "Besides, as argued previously, since there is a lot of wellbeing at stake in reducing catastrophic AI risks, consequentialist considerations assume a lot of weight.",
    "6I allow, however, that some people might, in accordance with a doing-allowing distinction [30], ascribe more weight to harms caused by an approach than prevented by it.",
    "This possibility is another reason to distinguish the desiderata in this way.Third, both the desideratum of degree of non-maleficence as well as beneficent side effects point to interactions between the question how best to reduce catastrophic AI risks and other issues in AI ethics.",
    "Approaches to catastrophic risks are, all things being equal, preferable if they also help with other problems identified in AI ethics, or -at least -do not cause what AI ethicists not focused on catastrophic risks would identify as harms.In the next two sections, we will put these desiderata to work."
  ]
}